  "texts": [
    "It is easy to see that MCES is NP-hard, as it generalizes subgraph isomorphism which, in turn, can be easily be reduced from the clique problem 99.",
    "See Raymond et al.",
    "26 from 2002 for an early and Englert et al.",
    "58 for a more recent discussion of the different problem variants as well as exact and heuristic algorithms for its solution.",
    "Exact methods guarantee that the MCES of two molecular structures is found, despite the computational hardness of the problem."
